article.headline: Lehigh 77, Lafayette 69
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Marquis Hall scored 24 points and helped Lehigh hold off a second-half rally for a 77-69 victory over Lafayette on Saturday. Bryan White added 13 points and Kyle Neptune had 12 for Lehigh (9-12, 4-1 Patriot League), which had a 37-21 lead at the half. Andrew Brown scored 30 points for Lafayette (7-13, 1-4), 20 of them in the second half. Lehigh jumped to a 15-4 lead and was ahead 23-7 with 8:29 remaining in the first half as Lafayette struggled, making only 25 percent of attempts and 3-for-15 from 3-point range. After the break, however, Brown led the Leopards to within three points on a 3-pointer with 1:39 remaining. Hall sank eight free throws in the final 1:19 to seal the win for the Mountain Hawks.
